result.execSummary:
Wade Edward Souster was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Wade Edward Souster was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: copy of criminal complaint and waiver of extradition mailed to Governor's office.
This did not take place. Court event needs to be in court record to dispose of case.

3:01 PM Wade Edward Souster appeared in custody from Jail via video,  Atty Liesl Nelson appeared in court, DA Halle E. Hatch appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court notes DE has a warrant out of Ramsey County Minnesota. Court confirms address, he is homeless. DE would like to waive extradition. DE understands possible penalties and constitutional rights. Court questions and reviews DE's rights. Court notes Deputy read the waiver to DE since he could not see it clearly.  DE signs WOE. Court adjourned at 3:11 pm.
